rComments: The best prof. I had in university so far. His lectures are amazing and just study from the lecture notes and notes you take in lecture and the problem sets/past tests. There are no surprises whatsoever. At the end of the exam he apologized because the average for the final was low (even though the test was fair) and curved the average to 73%

Really good professor, really good knowledge in a lot of different fields of Economics (Macro, Micro, econometrics). I liked the fat that he puts models (as ASAD or ISLM) in perpective. Most available professor I've ever have, so quick at answering questions in emails.
Best prof I've ever had. Go to every class and really know the material.

ECO349: Go to every lecture, otherwise you'll fall very behind. Test and exams are really difficult. Only thing that helps is a stock project to boost your mark. He expects you to know materials (which weren't taught) from 2nd year. Does many proofs, and you have to derive them on the exam. Quite a number of graphs as well.

A good prof. He constantly repeats that economics is harder than commerce and he's probably right. His lecture notes are important, especially the proofs he does and puts on the exams. He keeps the class average relatively high which is what most 4th year profs at universities such as UofT should do.

I took this course over the summer, and now I LOVE macro!!!! If you want to do well in this course than 1)do the readings and questions in the textbook 2)attend all lectures and make good notes. 3)past tests for eco208 and 202! The entire focus is on how a shock affects ur graphs.. if you can do that, you cannot end with a grade lower than 80!

Amazing professor- he is very helpful in the clas and his office hours. goes out of his way to help his students out- the math in the class shouldn't be loathed because he goes thru a mini lecture on the concepts before he dishes the complicated formulae out. Overall... one of the BEST ECO PROFS!

My first day of of eco 202 I saw a man walking through CCT and thought -what is that weirdo doing lurking around the school and you guessed it - it was professor gangon.  Love the jokes - love the outfits - not so much a fan of the lecture.
Lousy professor!!!!!! can't teach and thinks he's very funny. Tries to make simple things sounds difficult. He's just a sessional lecturer

very easy proff like Anderson.Lets you use a cheat sheet.Text book usage is minimal and you can get by on lectures.I got an 85%by Putting  in effort when listening to lecture and  study one hour after lecture .

He's a good example of the stereotypical economist and economic thoughts: very boring. His tests focus more on graphs and it's hard to do bad on. You should be able to get very far just by using your own logic and common sense. He seems like a math nerd and much of the proves he does in class don't appear on tests (for eco202)

A really nice guy. But he cracks me up because he's a small guy who wears sweaters that are three sizes too big and walks like an old man. Not an easy prof, but put in the necessary effort and you'll do fine.
Gagnon is loathed and Bailey is loved. Go figure. I don't get it. I must have missed the lectures when Gagnon acted like an ass and Bailey acted like an adult.
He's a very good economist, but not such a good lecturer.  Focus on your class notes and past tests, and just don't be afraid to ask questions, as he is fairly helpful.

sighs when lecturing but doesn't sigh at all when chatting personally on TTC. NEVER miss his class b/c tests=based on lec notes & aren't from the txtbook sometimes. study guide+hwk from txtbook=no need. practice w/ all past eco202 AND eco208 tests/exams, he recycles ques quite often for eco202 AND eco208. TA marks hard, but diff TA each yr *shrugs*
~a clever prof. Don't miss his lectures, class notes are crucial. Go for help if you need it, he'll be glad to help.~
Avoid him at all cost!!  i dont' think he's a good prof at all!
SIGHS EVERY TWO SECONDS...DONT KNOW WHY...HES GOOD AT WHAT HE DOES..BUT WE DONT KNOW WHAT HE DOES..LOL
he's the cure for all you insomniacs
